<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<knowl mode="exercise" xmlns="https://spatext.clontz.org" version="0.2">
    
 
        <intro>
            <p>A mysterious function <m>f(x,y)</m> has first partial derivatives</p>
            <p><me>f_x(x,y) = {{fx}}\qquad</me> and </p>
            <p><me>f_y(x,y) = {{fy}}\qquad</me>.
                </p>            
            <p>We don't know a formula for <m>f</m>, but we do know that <m>f({{x0}},{{y0}}) = {{z0}}.</m></p>
        </intro>
        
          <knowl>
            <content>
                <p>
                    Use linearization to approximate the value of <m>f({{x1}},{{y1}}).</m>
                </p>
            </content>
            <outtro>
                <p>
                   An approximate value is <m>{{z0}}+{{fx0}}({{dx}})+{{fy0}}({{dy}}) = {{z1}}</m>.
                </p>
             </outtro>
         </knowl>
        
        <knowl>
            <content>
                <p>
                    Find an equation for the tangent plane to the graph <m>z=f(x,y)</m> at <m>(x_0,y_0)=({{x0}},{{y0}})</m>.
                </p>
            </content>
            <outtro>
                <p>
                   <m>{{fx0}}({{xe}}) + {{fy0}}({{ye}}) - ({{ze}})=0</m>, or <m>{{planelhs}} = {{planerhs}}</m>.
                </p>
             </outtro>
         </knowl>
        

</knowl>